Zambian President Edgar Lungu says while the country welcomes international investors, the west should not dictate the terms when engaging with Africa on trade.  This comes at a time when the World Trade Organisation faces challenges after United States President Donald Trump lambasted the organisation. Many believe it is time for international investors to look to Africa as an alternative market. President Lungu spoke to South African Broadcasting Corporation’s Foreign Editor, Sophie Mokoena, in Livingston, Zambia on the sidelines of the Economic Summit. Watch video below 